 splanchnic veins: experience in 53 patients. <em>Transpl Int</em>1997; 10(2): 125–132.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1432-2277.1997.tb00554.x">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/9089998/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Transpl+Int&amp;publication_year=1997&amp;pages=125&amp;doi=10.1111%2Fj.1432-2277.1997.tb00554.x&amp;pmid=9089998">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">12.</div><div id="R12" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content"><span class="named-content" data-type="arthw-firstauthor"><span class="named-content" data-type="arthw-snm">Sugarbaker</span><span class="named-content" data-type="arthw-fnm">PH</span></span>, Nelson RC, Murray DR, Chezmar JL, Bernardino ME. A segmental approach to computerized tomographic portography for hepatic resection. <em>Surg Gynecol Obstet</em>1990; 171(3): 189–195.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/2385811/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Surg+Gynecol+Obstet&amp;publication_year=1990&amp;pages=189&amp;pmid=2385811">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">13.</div><div id="R13" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content"><span class="named-content" data-type="arthw-firstauthor"><span class="named-content" data-type="arthw-snm">Cheng</span><span class="named-content" data-type="arthw-fnm">YF</span></span>, Huang TL, Lee TY, Chen TY, Chen CL. Variation of the intrahepatic portal vein: angiographic demonstration and application in living-related hepatic transplantation. <em>Transplant Proc</em>199