 class="named-content" data-type="arthw-firstauthor"><span class="named-content" data-type="arthw-snm">Hirao</span><span class="named-content" data-type="arthw-fnm">K</span></span>, Miyazaki A, Fujimoto T, Isomoto I, Hayashi K. Evaluation of aberrant bile ducts before laparoscopic cholecystectomy: helical CT cholangiography versus MR cholangiography. <em>AJR Am J Roentgenol</em>2000; 175(3): 713–720.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.2214/ajr.175.3.1750713">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/10954455/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=AJR+Am+J+Roentgenol&amp;publication_year=2000&amp;pages=713&amp;doi=10.2214%2Fajr.175.3.1750713&amp;pmid=10954455">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div></div></section></div></section></div><div class="core-collateral" role="dialog" aria-modal="true"><div id="core-collateral-info" data-active-pane="false"><header><h2><i class="icon-info" aria-hidden="true"></i>Information &amp; Authors</h2></header><section id="tab-information" role="tabpanel"><h3>Information</h3><section class="core-self-citation"><h4>Published In</h4><div class="core-journal-presentation">



        
        <div class="cover-image flat d-flex justify-content-center flex-column"><div data-is-viewable="" class="cover-image__image"><a href="/toc/radiographics/28/2" title="Go to RadioGraphics " class="d-block"><img src="/cms/10.1148/radiographics.2008.28.issue-2/asset/14a1685b-ce14-1685-ace1-a1685bace14a/radiographics.2008.28.issue-2.cover.gif" alt="Go to RadioGraphics " loading="lazy"/></a></div></div>
<div class="core-journal-description"><div property="isPartOf" typeof="Periodical"><span property="name">RadioGraphics</span></div><div class="core-enumeration"><span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationVolume">Volume <span property="volumeNumber">28</span></span> • <span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationIssue">Number <span property="issueNumber">2</span></span> • <span property="datePublished">Mar 1 2008</span></div><div class="core-pagination"><span class="heading">Pages</span>: <span class="content"><span property="pageStart">359</span> - <span property="pageEnd">378</span></span></div><div class="core-pmid"><span class="heading">PubMed</span>: <a class="content" href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/18349445/" property="sameAs" target="_blank" title="Link to PubMed">18349445</a></div></div></div></section><section class="core-copyright"><h4>Copyright</h4><div role="paragraph">© RSNA, 2008.</div></section><section class="core-history"><h4>History</h4><div><b class="core-label">Published online</b>: Mar 1 2008</div></section><section class="core-permissions"><h4>Permissions</h4><div>Request permissions for this article.</div><div><a class="btn" href="https://marketplace.copyright.com/rs-ui-web/mp/search/all/10.1148%2Frg.282075099">Request Permissions</a></div></section><section property="keywords"><h4>Keywords</h4><ol><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=BOPTA+%3D+benzyloxypropionictetraacetate&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">BOPTA = benzyloxypropionictetraacetate</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=HAIP+%3D+hepatic+arterial+infusion+pump&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">HAIP = hepatic arterial infusion pump</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=IVC+%3D+inferior+vena+cava&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">IVC = inferior vena cava</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=MIP+%3D+maximum+intensity+projection&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">MIP = maximum intensity projection</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=3D+%3D+three-dimensional&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">3D = three-dimensional</a></li></ol></section><section class="core-article-notes"><h4>Notes</h4><div role="paragraph">Use of multidetector CT angiography, MR angiography, and MR cholangiography for evaluation of hepatic arterial, hepatic venous, portal venous, and bile duct variants is described, with emphasis on their relevance to hepatic surgery.</div></section></section><section id="tab-contributors" role="tabpanel"><h3>Authors</h3><section class="core-authors"><h4>Affiliations</h4><div id="con1" property="author" typeof="Person"><div class="heading"><span property="givenName">Onofrio A.</span> <span property="familyName">Catalano</span>, <span property="honorificSuffix">MD</span></div><div class="content"><div class="affiliations"><div property="affiliation" typeof="Organization"><span property="name">From the Department of Radiology, Division of Abdominal Imaging and Intervention (O.A.C., A.H.S., R.N.U., P.F.H., D.V.S.), and Department of Surgery (C.R.F.), Massachusetts General Hospital, 55 Fruit St, WHT 270, Boston, MA 02114. Presented as an education exhibit at the 2006 RSNA Annual Meeting. Received May 4, 2007; revision requested June 15 and received June 29; accepted July 3. D.V.S. receives research support from General Electric and consults for the Bracco Group; all other authors have no financial relationships to disclose.</span></div></div><div class="core-author-link"><a href="/authored-by/Catalano/Onofrio+A" rel="nofollow">View all articles by this author</a></div></div></div><div id="con2" property="author" typeof="Person"><div class="heading"><span property="givenName">Anandkumar H.</span> <span property="family